race.comment: GOLD CAPITAL (14) went close from the back at Muswellbrook in Maidens and then came back to this trip and hit the line hard, winning a 50 at Armidale as expected. May have to do it the hard way, but he comes back home and is capable of taking the next step. AFRICAN DIAMOND (9) led and was an easy Maiden winner over 1280m at Muswellbrook first-up. Is lightly raced and has plenty of scope for improvement. This is a bit tougher, but she cannot be underestimated. JAGERSCHNITZEL (6) broke Maidens at Dubbo and then pushed on from a wide barrier at Beaumont Newcastle, beaten 1L as favourite. Morgan sticks aboard, and he can bounce without surprise. Wary of ZUCCHERO (1) on resumption, and the race-day betting will be key with him. He will race over further, but it's hard to risk the lethal Bullock-Messara & Gavranich linkage. Has trialled twice and has the inside barrier.
